import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('ohlc.json')

# Plot histogram of opening prices
sns.histplot(data=data, x='open', kde=True, color='blue')
plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
plt.legend()
plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?')
plt.xlabel('Opening Price')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('ohlc.json')

# Convert date field to datetime type
data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

# Calculate average daily volume traded
daily_volume = data.groupby(data['date'].dt.date)['volume'].sum().mean()

# Create bar chart of daily volume traded
sns.barplot(x=data['date'].dt.date, y=data['volume'], color='blue')

# Add average daily volume traded line
plt.axhline(y=daily_volume, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average daily volume traded: {daily_volume:.2f}')

# Set chart title and axis labels
plt.title('What is the average daily volume traded?')
plt.xlabel('Date')
plt.ylabel('Volume')

# Rotate x-axis labels for legibility
plt.xticks(rotation=45)

# Add legend
plt.legend()

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('ohlc.json')

# Convert date field to datetime type
data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

# Create scatter plot
sns.scatterplot(x='close', y='volume', data=data)

# Set chart title
plt.title('What is the correlation between closing prices and volume traded?', wrap=True)

# Show plot
plt.show()

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_json('ohlc.json')

# Convert date field to datetime type
data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

# Set chart style
sns.set_style('darkgrid')

# Create histogram of daily high prices
sns.histplot(data=data, x='high', kde=True, color='blue')

# Add vertical line for median
median = data['high'].median()
plt.axvline(median, color='red', linestyle='dashed', label=f'Median: {median:.2f}')

# Set chart title and labels
plt.title('What is the distribution of daily high prices?')
plt.xlabel('Daily High Prices')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

# Add legend
plt.legend()

# Show plot
plt.show()
```
